                <p>We may update, improve, suspend, or discontinue parts of MapleKiosk as needed. We work to keep the service reliable, but we do not promise uninterrupted access.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Liability</h2>
                <p>MapleKiosk is provided as available. To the extent allowed by law, we are not responsible for indirect losses such as lost profits, revenue, data, or business opportunities.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Termination</h2>
                <p>You may stop using MapleKiosk at any time. We may suspend or end access if these terms are violated, fees are unpaid, or continued use creates legal, security, or operational risk.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Contact</h2>
                <p>For questions about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@maplekiosk.com">legal@maplekiosk.com</a>.</p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>

<Footer />

@code {
    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        var uri = new Uri(Nav.Uri);
        var seg = uri.AbsolutePath.Trim('/').Split('/').FirstOrDefault() ?? "";
        L.SetCulture(seg);
    }
}
